First Solar to Borrow $176 million to Expand German Solar Plant

-- B y   A n d r e w   H e r n d o n
-- 
2011-05-24T20:18:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/first-solar-to-borrow-176-million-to-expand-german-thin-film-solar-plant.html
First Solar Inc. (FSLR) , the world’s largest
producer of thin-film solar panels, is borrowing money to expand
a production facility in Germany.  The 124.5 million euro ($175.6 million) credit agreement
with  Commerzbank AG (CBK)  will finance the purchase of land in
Frankfurt an der Oder, Germany, and to build a production line,
Tempe, Arizona-based First Solar said today in a regulatory
filing. The company expects to double to 446 megawatts the
plant’s annual production capacity, by the fourth quarter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Herndon in San Franisco at 
 aherndon2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  